The paper focuses on studying behavior of developers and software projects in large open source ecosystems, specifically on GitHub. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the potential threats to mining large open source datasets, which could fall under the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper proposes a method for detecting public development projects, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
